Files containing the handler implementations for admin_api (paths relative to project root):

Explanation:
- app/api/cms/__init__.py imports admin_api from app.api.cms.admin and registers it under the /admin prefix.
- The Blueprint object admin_api and all of its route handler functions are defined in app/api/cms/admin.py (it declares admin_api = Blueprint("admin", __name__) and contains the @admin_api.route(...) handlers).
- I searched the repository for other definitions/usages of admin_api and found no other files that define the admin_api blueprint, so app/api/cms/admin.py is the single implementation file.
